Two years ago , i adopted this little fur ball when its owner was about to abandon him at the SPCA, an animal refuge.

When I saw him, I fell in love with him despite the fact that he was a stressed, anxious and frightened dog. His former master did not care about him or his health.

Today, Koutchi is no longer the same; he is cheerful, affectionate and who day by day knows the real life of a dog, he quickly became a member of our family.

In about three weeks, Koutchi will undergo surgery to remove a cyst that keeps growing, but also a scaling followed by extraction of one or more teeth.

Veterinary care is not provided and I also know that because of this pandemic, financially, it is not easy; a donation would be welcome, but if you cannot contribute, this is completely understandable.
